      <section id="id42574238">
        <title>ACTIVITY: To describe the composition of substances in terms of chemical symbols and formulas [LO 2.3]</title>
        <para id="id42389899">When we know the physical and chemical properties of a substance we can use our knowledge to create another substance. Water, a compound, is the best solvent because many substances can dissolve in water. We can use the compound water to obtain gases like hydrogen and oxygen. We can also produce water by mixing these gases.</para>
        <para id="id42494250">We make use of chemical symbols to identify elements and use chemical formulas to identify compounds. Here are some chemical symbols:</para>
        <list id="id42494258" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>Ag (symbol) is used for silver</item>
          <item>Fe is used for iron</item>
          <item>Pb is used for lead</item>
          <item>Au is used for gold</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id42291279">Try to illustrate the composition of a water molecule:</para>
        <list id="id42291284" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>Write the chemical formula for water.</item>
        </list>
