      <section id="id46743332">
        <title>ASSIGNMENT 2</title>
        <para id="id46743339">Now try to analyse the chemical formula for carbon dioxide (carbonic acid gas):</para>
        <para id="id42364069">Carbon dioxide is a compound of two kinds of atoms. The chemical formula is:</para>
        <para id="id42891358">CO2</para>
        <para id="id42891362">
          <emphasis effect="bold">CO</emphasis>
          <emphasis effect="bold">2</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para id="id42444562">This formula signifies that one atom of carbon combines with two atoms of oxygen to form carbon dioxide. We can therefore say that the ratio of carbon atoms to oxygen atoms in carbon dioxide molecules is 1:2.</para>
